[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test environments**\n\nI'm considering how to create tests that can work effectively in a JVM. It seems like they need to check if the environment has a display, and it has to be compatible natively too for robustness. There's a public API for `WindowUtils.getAlphaCompatibleGraphicsConfiguration`, but I realize it might not be used in non-X11 environments. Perhaps I should run tests with an Xvfb setup on Linux. I wonder how that would impact the results in a headless context.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_051a386868a8f19b016a10a184ab64819eb7188c45a8c4f319\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEKGH8jWD2NI6BkYpZacmyHTJMBNnRm3ZZ57hSSe6iBootZ3DL8bN0ByTjfhrfcBzXk7Y76G8figUJC3RzWbhHgNFe1MwusTZ5C0b9Bxrzpa6lewTpfGJ9hdmHDGg15t0dc8yt-UUZ0oVePx6e0yq9ieV8mHrQ398V0Cpaaor6OL_0uk96KNyue_qgij8utXCbcv3NKqkiULp5SNX3E8Wl89UXl7BTLB6Cpq9KWxYodXAbAMDVRgB7lnLDqdM1f8f5LV25-7ldW9YE9tkb5JDNeG1GLBWQkCHAvH2t1yvkMVpNu6LBqyGy_8j_fdjN8VXrsuBTjJhHkXpjTrkYaCSQZ78HK5ZHrkm1Y-OnBpH0-_U6tGvunf_B_ienkbEc5jrCfv1kLEBqLgVdstumTnZD_G-bz2sEI6QCjnFES_Mc8RVR1P9exJfx7X-rdmoHSaxrHT6dJH4rWt4b2HyxeRZwZ8aANuxBkZv_U7lOr1u_fVnsrLfnaHUeVjHQtHpi_owGEDEJY0w_iEqjzWJdIGsbfZfIOEdgROFwLOeDUiGnqCw3vzxEuCSbzXV0pHf1reD9AG0JlWt4tsbC7GnJTWil7ZM_eN641JMQ0KvRRrskjGBo_6qKh3Gmqg_ooxikdTpG2hVeoK0ODszN-72DfneHC2vJXnSBIwWSF5wtDh5mKmW3GIOPlElmyElp8myz027gwZBcnayp-DDuwEAliAdhnoHbud2Ta1gweEF3A7uqPV14aHZ045M1ftiMsdTgVN83qX6fkXlk4qxR80MtmDgJp9uXoNUlIwe1tJzu7VMjSkFHNl_WhUCEAbO70aFxym23FFklIxkUj_p882Lq0PA2Gc4R8c4CNn1no9nqCECS4QHxvcNrsrbo6861idAXXhWoAuVj6RN7oG9snDUmMwa29lY3Tw8rkRbNUDuoOkIjw8blraj4Kbor8r75pRnsmFLK5zJdTPbeU1svlwzxlle538zHnWsIyjMjMOSog9dG6rp58jduRJqztNySOME3XmvGgkrw9T2Xd5i0yYdhq086xLdLBXSlFzmkmRX85nEnVg_x-a6wke3T-szEd8vQ3g-dG8CAmkZNcU4d3oMhR3xtmTbHhbxRiE3gmiD6ROLmYotgsVGBWqj0CtLt6bOp-rDyc4ku5aDFfMRJTJf5DAmRf_PGHqCrpGMhbbMg3KmWIho2b8GYQkslgtay3_SEQ1BWNUprkfUvjgcnAKnTwc4wakDOy7QT2jFemFqZT