nment. But with JDK after 17 and sealed packages, it looks challenging. More trouble than it's worth?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering window transparency**\\n\\nI'm exploring X11WindowUtils.getAlphaVisualIDs, which uses native calls instead of AWT. It seems impossible to force alphaVisualIDs without reflection. I wonder if I could use the public API setWindowTransparent with a real Frame after starting Xvfb, but maybe it requires a UI. I think getAlphaCompatible might be a better option. I should also check if the container or test environment includes Xvfb to confirm whether it can support my needs.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nfTTlDLEFgISuUgjtNGj3FnY|fc_051a386868a8f19b016a10a1a720d8819ebd97d323a915b11a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "which Xvfb || true; echo DISPLAY=$DISPLAY; xdpyinfo >/tmp/xdpyinfo.out 2>/tmp/xdpyinfo.err; echo $?; head -5 /tmp/xdpyinfo.err /tmp/xdpyinfo.out 2>/dev/null"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 547, "output": 859, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29566, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779474839843, "responseId": "resp_051a386868a8f19b016a10a1985480819e91d5ce10bcf87ade"}}
